div.div:
PSP Core System
Keeps general information about merchants, transactions, supported methods of payment. Allows merchants to configure methods of payment through a single unified API (YAML configuration).

div.div:
PSP Payment Handlers
Keep information about merchants and transactions that is specific to the particular method of payment (e.g. crypto handler keeps track of deposit addresses). Each exposes internal API to the PSP Core that is built according to the Core's requirements, and defines configuration schema for configuring the payment method via YAML file.

Merchant Client Apps
Keep their own track of transactions and payments. Communicate with PSP to initialize transactions and expose a callback endpoint for receiving latest updates about pending transactions.

Customers
Customers start by browsing goods and services on the merchant's website, then get redirected to the payment method choosing dialog, then payment screen, and finally back to the merchant's website.

External Systems
Transaction processing is done on external systems that offer ways of initiating transactions and checking the transaction status. Each PSP Payment Handler is built around the external systems to provide their functionality to the PSP.
